![](data:image/png;base64,)

The **Check and Build **tab lists all builds and validations, both ongoing and complete, and allows to perform the following operations:

- **Build: **Create the final package to be used for the generation of the printing spool of the final document.

-  **Validation: **Check the entire project, including every element configured in the other views.

- **Search through builds and tests: **Search build and checks launched in the last five days, with different search methods.

> Warning

*The build and validation processes only apply to approved documents.*

*For more information, see: Document Selection and Approval.*

## Starting the operation
- Select a **Profile **from the drop-down menu.

> Note

*For more information, see: Profiles Tab*

- Click:

**Start validation **button to start the validation of all approved documents in the project

- **Start build **to start the build process

An animated icon showing Operation in progress appears:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

and a new row is appended to the table with an "Ongoing" label in the status cell.

> Note

*The system performs a preliminary check before releasing the package for the creation of the document.*

When the operation is completed, a yellow popup like the following one appears for some seconds at the top of the interface:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

and the status icon displays the result of the operation:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

The operation status in the corresponding cell of the table changes to "Completed" or "Failed".

> Note

*Both the build and validation operations can take several minutes to complete. For this reason, they are processed on the server, in order not to freeze the user interface.*

## Viewing information on builds and validations
![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Information**

**Description**

**Code**

Operation code, automatically generated by the system

**Operation**

the operation that has been performed. It may assume one of the following values:

- **Validation **

- **Build**

**Profile**

The profile that has been used at build or validation time.

**Start Date**

The date the operation has been started

**End Date**

The date the operation has finished

**Status**

The status of the operation. It may assume one of the following values:

- **Ongoing**: the operation is still in progress

- **Failed/Completed**: the operation has (un)successfully completed. If you click on it it will pop up a Report similar to the following one:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

> Note

*The report icons and buttons are just like the ones described in Preview View.*

**User**

The user that started the operation

**Documents**

The number of documents of the build

**Download**

In case a build operation is completed successfully click on the **download ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)** icon to download a ZIP file with the build files.

The zip file is named: *&lt;Client&gt;_&lt;Procedure&gt;_&lt;Application&gt;_&lt;Environment&gt;_&lt;Version&gt;.zip*

> Note

*For more information, see: Exporting DT and DC resources from the Doxee Platform.*

## **Filtering information**
Use the drop-down menu on the table headers to filter the content of the table.

## Refreshing data
To refresh the contents of the table, click ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Refresh Data**).
